                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/888: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-12T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 12—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>870. Legation’s 854, December 3, 4 p.m. Following from Canton: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 12, 10 a.m. Standard Oil Company lighters released yesterday
                            afternoon on written assurance from me that company ‘would be held to
                            strict accountability under any decision reached through due process of
                            law’.</p>
                        <p>Lighters and cargoes were held exactly two months and, in my opinion,
                            would never have been released if Marshal Li had not returned. Despatch
                            follows.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
